This paper deals with the problem of inconsistency in pairwise comparison matrices, which is a common issue in multi-criteria decision making. The paper presents new results on inconsistency indices and their relationship with the quality of priority vector estimation. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including cs.MS (mathematical software), cs.AI (artificial intelligence), cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.LG (machine learning), and cs.SI (social and information networks). However, given the focus on decision making and optimization, cs.MS and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.DS, cs.LG, and cs.SI.
